players.name: Jesús Owono
players.summary: Jesús Lázaro Owono Ngua Akeng is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Segunda División club FC Andorra, on loan from La Liga club Alavés, and the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Aitor Embela
players.summary: Aitor Mbela Gil, known in Spain as Aitor Embela Gil, is a professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Tercera Federación club Soneja. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Manuel Sapunga
players.summary: Manuel Sapunga Mbara is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for South African Premiership club Sekhukhune United and the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Néstor Senra
players.summary: Néstor Senra Pérez is a footballer who plays as a right back for Segunda Federación club Recreativo. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Marvin Anieboh
players.summary: Marvin José Anieboh Pallaruelo is a professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Segunda Federación club SS Reyes. Born in Spain, he represents Equatorial Guinea internationally.

players.name: Basilio Ndong
players.summary: Basilio Ndong Owono Nchama is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays for Kategoria Superiore club Tirana and the Equatorial Guinea national team. Mainly a left back, he can also operate as a left winger.

players.name: Charles Ondo
players.summary: Charles Nduwuisi Ondo is a professional footballer who plays as a left-back for MLS Next Pro club Portland Timbers 2. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Carlos Akapo
players.summary: Carlos Akapo Martínez is a professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Campeonato Brasileiro Série B club Amazonas. Born in Spain, he represents Equatorial Guinea at international level.

players.name: Saúl Coco
players.summary: Saúl Basilio Coco-Bassey Oubiña, better known as Saúl Coco, is a professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Serie A club Torino and the Equatorial Guinea national team. Born in Spain, he represents Equatorial Guinea at international level, debuting for the senior team in 2017.

players.name: Michael Ngaah
players.summary: Michael Ngaah Bosio, sometimes known as Prince, is a professional footballer who plays as a left-back for Segunda Federación club Real Ávila. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Esteban Obiang
players.summary: Esteban Orozco Fernández, also known simply as Esteban, is a professional footballer who plays as a defender or a defensive midfielder for Liga I club Argeș Pitești. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Álex Balboa
players.summary: Alejandro 'Álex' Balboa Bandeira is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Primera Federación club Lugo. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Omar Mascarell
players.summary: Omar Mascarell González is a professional footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for La Liga club Mallorca.

players.name: José Machín
players.summary: José Ndong Machín Dicombo, also known as Pepín, is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays as an attacking midfielder for Serie C club Vis Pesaro the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Jannick Buyla
players.summary: Jannick Buyla Sam is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Segunda Federación club Numancia. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Pedro Obiang
players.summary: Pedro Mba Obiang Avomo is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Serie B club Monza and the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Santiago Eneme
players.summary: Santiago Eneme Bocari is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Czech First League club Sparta Prague and the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Pablo Ganet
players.summary: Pablo Ganet Comitre is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Indonesian Super League club Persita Tangerang. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Gael Joel Akogo
players.summary: Gael Joel Akogo Esono Nchama, sometimes known as Gael Joel or just Gael, is an Equatoguinean footballer who plays as a midfielder for Segunda Federación club Recreativo Granada and the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Álex Masogo
players.summary: Alejandro Martín Masogo is a professional footballer who plays as midfielder for Bulgarian First League club Beroe Stara Zagora. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Iban Salvador
players.summary: Iván Salvador Edú, known in Spain as Iban Salvador and in Africa as Iban Edú, is a professional footballer who plays as a forward for Ekstraklasa club Wisła Płock. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Dorian Jr.
players.summary: Dorian Junior Hanza Meha is a professional footballer who plays as a forward for Danish Superliga club Viborg. Born in Spain, he represents Equatorial Guinea at international level.

players.name: Emilio Nsue
players.summary: Emilio Nsue López is a professional footballer who plays for Segunda Federación club Intercity. Born in Spain, he is the captain and all-time leading scorer of the Equatorial Guinea national team. A versatile player, he plays mainly as a right-back but can also play as a winger.

players.name: Josete Miranda
players.summary: José Antonio Miranda Boacho, known as Josete Miranda or simply Josete, is a professional footballer who plays as a forward for Super League Greece 2 club Kalamata. Born in Spain, he plays for the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Luis Nlavo
players.summary: Luis Miguel Nlavo Asué, known in Equatorial Guinea as Luis Nlavo, is an Equatoguinean professional footballer who plays as a forward for Chinese Super League club Shanghai Shenhua and the Equatorial Guinea national team.

players.name: Loren Zúñiga
players.summary: Lorenzo "Loren" Zúñiga Owono is a professional footballer who plays as a striker for Primera Federación club Real Madrid Castilla. Born in Spain, he represents Equatorial Guinea at international level.

players.name: José Nabil Ondo
players.summary: José Nabil Ondó Onvá Adjugu is an Equatoguinean footballer who plays as a striker for Championnat National 3 club Nantes II and the Equatorial Guinea national team.
